# Phase 28 Implementation Plan: Presentation Settings Font Size and Monitor Pane Pin/Unpin

This plan details the implementation of presentation setting updates (supporting font sizes up to 300, exact preview screens) and the addition of VS Code-style pin/unpin auto-hide functionality with a sleek bottom rail for the Monitor 1 and Monitor 2 panes.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **No State Persistence**: Following the design of the Library pane (Songs/Bible search), the pin mode and visibility state of the Monitor pane will not be persisted to disk. On app restart, the pane will default to pinned + visible. 
> 
> **Overlay Height**: In auto-hide mode, the Monitor pane overlay will occupy a fixed height of `250px` positioned directly above the bottom bar, spanning the full width of the Right column. It will include a subtle drop shadow on its top edge to indicate it is a floating panel.

---

