### 6. Sleek Monitor Bottom Bar
Implement the bottom horizontal bar that allows users to toggle visibility and switch tabs.

#### [NEW] [monitor_bottom_bar.dart](file:///c:/Users/bhanu/projects/KeryxPro/lib/features/dashboard/presentation/widgets/monitor_bottom_bar.dart)
- Create a new horizontal widget `MonitorBottomBar`:
  - Height: `28`
  - Background: `Colors.grey[900]`
  - Centered Row containing two icon buttons for Monitor 1 and Monitor 2.
  - Buttons use a stacked widget: outline monitor icon (`Icons.monitor`, size 18) with a centered digit `1` or `2` (size 7, bold).
  - Selected state shows a bottom accent border (height 2, color blue) and highlighted white color (inactive color is `white38`).
  - Tapping behaves identically to `LibraryIconRail`:
    - Tapping same active tab when pane is visible hides the pane.
    - Tapping inactive tab when pane is visible switches active tab.
    - Tapping any tab when pane is hidden makes it visible and switches to that tab.

